# Default flags for `act` (https://github.com/nektos/act).
#
# - `-P ubuntu-latest=...` swaps act's tiny default image for catthehacker's
#   `act-latest`, which carries the apt packages most GH-hosted runners
#   ship with (curl, git, build-essential, etc.) so our deployment.yaml's
#   "Install host build tools" step doesn't have to fight a barebones
#   image.
# - `--container-architecture linux/amd64` is the right default even on
#   ARM hosts (theos toolchain + L1ghtmann iOSToolchain only publish
#   x86_64 binaries; running them via Rosetta/qemu beats not running them
#   at all).
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest
--container-architecture linux/amd64
